{
  "number": 1756,
  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/1756",
  "title": "Is there a way to hide the search results when clicking on a search result?",
  "body": "I currently want the following behavior:\r\n- When you click on a search result, it hides the result and ideally clears the input field\r\n- When you type in the search field and then lose focus or click outside the search field or search results list, it hides the results list\r\n\r\nCurrently I'm just using `onBlur` to get the desired result, but unfortunately I had to change a lot of my handlers to `onMouseDown` since `onBlur` fires before `onClick`. Also when using the `InfiniteHits` widget, clicking on `Load More` automatically closes my results list and doesn't fire due to the `onBlur`.\r\n\r\nI know you have a `ClearAll` widget, but it's a separate button and it would be nice to have access to a `clearField` method or something to manually trigger that when I want based on custom behavior.\r\n\r\nLet me know if there is a way to take care of the above though.\r\n\r\nThanks!\r\n\r\nTed",
